1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:01,760
So this is a very exciting day because
于是今天是个非常激动人心的日子，因为

2
00:00:01,760 --> 00:00:06,600
we are officially starting the Gay to Lease journalism course.
我们正式开始了《盖伊·托·里斯》新闻学课程。

3
00:00:06,980 --> 00:00:09,560
Traditionally, we've understood journalism and
传统上，我们把新闻学理解为

4
00:00:09,560 --> 00:00:13,400
research as this method of just collecting information,
研究就是这种只收集信息的方法

5
00:00:13,920 --> 00:00:16,620
organizing it, and then expressing it.
组织它，然后表达它。

6
00:00:16,920 --> 00:00:21,680
But then along came a man named Gay to Lease, and he transformed journalism.
随后出现了一个叫盖伊·托·里斯的人，他改变了新闻学。

7
00:00:21,960 --> 00:00:25,960
He transformed the way we understood research. So
他改变了我们对研究的理解。

8
00:00:25,960 --> 00:00:31,820
we created something called literary journalism,
我们创造了一种叫作家新闻的东西

9
00:00:32,200 --> 00:00:34,860
which is the idea
这就是想法

10
00:00:34,860 --> 00:00:39,160
that journalism can be by itself be literature.
新闻本身就能成为文学。

11
00:00:40,200 --> 00:00:44,760
The Gay to Lease method is going to teach us how to be creative, how to be imaginative,
盖伊·托·里斯方法将教会我们如何创造性、如何想象性

12
00:00:45,280 --> 00:00:49,300
and how to engage with reality
以及如何与现实互动

13
00:00:49,300 --> 00:00:50,700
and engage with people.
并与人互动。

14
00:00:50,860 --> 00:00:52,540
We don't teach you this in school.
我们在学校里没有教你这个。

15
00:00:52,680 --> 00:00:53,880
In fact, we teach you the opposite.
实际上，我们教你的是相反的。

16
00:00:54,080 --> 00:00:57,260
We teach you the opposite. Don't explore. Just do what the teacher tells you to do.
我们教你的是相反的。别去探索，直接按老师说的去做。

17
00:00:57,480 --> 00:01:01,200
Where did he learn this? Well, he learned this at home.
他是从哪里学到的？嗯，学的就是在家里。

18
00:01:02,280 --> 00:01:04,140
The reason why is that
原因是因为……

19
00:01:04,140 --> 00:01:07,300
his father was a tailor.
他的父亲是一名裁缝师。

20
00:01:09,500 --> 00:01:11,300
His father was a tailor.
他的父亲是一名裁缝师。

21
00:01:13,680 --> 00:01:19,620
And he had a tailoring business in New Jersey.
他在新泽西有一家裁缝生意。

22
00:01:20,140 --> 00:01:21,480
And his mother...
他的母亲……

23
00:01:24,560 --> 00:01:27,940
took care of the business while his father made the clothes.
在父亲制作衣服时，他负责处理业务。

24
00:01:29,120 --> 00:01:33,780
So what does this have to do with exploration and reflection?
那这跟探索与反思有什么关系呢？

25
00:01:35,820 --> 00:01:40,700
Well, his mother was responsible for the business aspects.
好的，母亲负责店铺的业务。

26
00:01:41,060 --> 00:01:44,960
So these very wealthy people would come to the shop
于是这些非常富裕的人会来店里。

27
00:01:44,960 --> 00:01:47,820
and order very nice suits.
并订购非常好的西装。

28
00:01:49,280 --> 00:01:53,760
And her job was to deal with them.
她的工作就是与他们打交道。

29
00:01:53,760 --> 00:01:57,140
But it's actually very hard to deal with rich people.
但实际上与富人打交道非常难。

30
00:01:57,320 --> 00:01:58,580
They can be very demanding.
它们可能非常苛刻。

31
00:01:59,260 --> 00:02:01,900
So her strategy was to become their friend.
于是她的策略就是成为他们的朋友。

32
00:02:02,580 --> 00:02:04,380
And how do you become someone's friend?
[32] 那么你怎么才能成为别人的朋友？

33
00:02:04,680 --> 00:02:06,960
What do you do in order to become someone's friend?
[33] 你要做什么才能成为别人的朋友？

34
00:02:07,260 --> 00:02:08,640
What must you do? Talk.
你要做什么？说话。

35
00:02:10,400 --> 00:02:12,280
Wrong. Not talk.
错。不是说话。

36
00:02:12,540 --> 00:02:14,820
The opposite. Listen.
相反。听着。

37
00:02:15,140 --> 00:02:17,240
Okay? Do you understand? So...
好的？你明白吗？所以…

38
00:02:20,880 --> 00:02:23,740
In the family living room, the mother would say,
在客厅里，妈妈会说，

39
00:02:23,740 --> 00:02:25,440
I want to sit down on the
我想坐在……上

40
00:02:25,440 --> 00:02:30,520
couch talking with these very wealthy people.
沙发上与这些非常富有的人交谈。

41
00:02:31,440 --> 00:02:33,220
And she would talk just by listening.
她只靠倾听来交谈。

42
00:02:34,020 --> 00:02:37,360
Okay? So her strategy for this is
好？她的做法是

43
00:02:37,360 --> 00:02:42,960
that I am interested in you.
我对你有兴趣。

44
00:02:44,440 --> 00:02:48,180
So that's how she became friends with all these very wealthy people,
于是她就和这些富有的人交朋友了。

45
00:02:48,360 --> 00:02:50,120
even though she herself was not wealthy.
即使她自己不富有。

46
00:02:50,300 --> 00:02:52,660
She had a mindset that
她有一种心态，

47
00:02:52,660 --> 00:02:56,080
whoever came into her living room,
无论谁走进她的客厅，

48
00:02:56,180 --> 00:02:57,540
whoever was a client,
谁是客户，

49
00:02:58,720 --> 00:03:00,620
was first and foremost a friend.
先是朋友。

50
00:03:00,840 --> 00:03:03,440
And she was interested in this person.
她对那个人很感兴趣。

51
00:03:03,580 --> 00:03:05,020
She was interested in people.
她对人很感兴趣。

52
00:03:05,340 --> 00:03:07,920
So she would spend hours and hours just listening to that
于是她会花上好几个小时，只是听那个人说说说。

53
00:03:07,920 --> 00:03:10,620
person talk and talk and talk.
她会花上好几个小时，只是听那个人说说说。

54
00:03:11,100 --> 00:03:13,480
And so you can say that this is exploration.
于是你可以说这是探索。

55
00:03:17,500 --> 00:03:19,560
Curiosity. Okay?
好奇。

56
00:03:19,680 --> 00:03:22,000
Exploration. But in the other room,
探索。可是在另一间房间，

57
00:03:22,000 --> 00:03:25,140
the father would by himself sit
父亲会亲自坐在那儿。

58
00:03:25,140 --> 00:03:27,300
and work on the clothes.
并且在衣服上工作。

59
00:03:27,500 --> 00:03:29,980
Right? I'm not sure if you've seen Taylor's work.
对吧？我不确定你是否看过泰勒的作品。

60
00:03:30,240 --> 00:03:31,640
They are very precise.
他们非常精准。

61
00:03:32,160 --> 00:03:33,540
They are very exact.
他们非常准确。

62
00:03:33,920 --> 00:03:35,460
They are very meticulous.
他们非常细致。

63
00:03:36,440 --> 00:03:37,680
They're very disciplined.
他们非常有纪律。

64
00:03:37,920 --> 00:03:40,840
They're very patient. So he could spend days
他们非常耐心。于是他可以在房间里花上几天时间专注于一件西装。

65
00:03:40,840 --> 00:03:45,380
and days in his room just working on a piece of suit.
他可以在房间里花上几天时间专注于一件西装。

66
00:03:46,080 --> 00:03:48,060
Right? This is the idea of reflection.
对吧？这就是反思的概念。

67
00:03:52,000 --> 00:03:53,260
The pursuit of perfection.
追求完美。

68
00:03:58,060 --> 00:04:00,600
So exploration is the pursuit of curiosity.
探索是好奇心的追求。

69
00:04:05,540 --> 00:04:08,100
And reflection is the pursuit of perfection.
反思是完美的追求。

70
00:04:08,880 --> 00:04:14,120
This is a Gay Talese research method.
这是一种《Gay Talese》研究方法。

71
00:04:14,240 --> 00:04:15,640
This is what I'll be teaching you.
这就是我要教给你的内容。

72
00:04:15,780 --> 00:04:19,440
This is something that will not just help you become a better writer,
这不仅能让你写作更好，也会让你更具创意、更有效的研究者。

73
00:04:19,440 --> 00:04:23,360
but someone who will be much more creative and a much more effective researcher.
这将使你成为更好的作家，并且更具创意、更有效的研究者。

74
00:04:23,920 --> 00:04:26,540
So even if you are going to the sciences,
所以即使你去科学领域，我保证你在这门课学到的技能无论去哪里都能派上用场。

75
00:04:26,920 --> 00:04:31,700
I guarantee you that the skills you'll be learning in this class will help you wherever you go.
我保证你在这门课学到的技能无论去哪里都能派上用场。

76
00:04:31,940 --> 00:04:35,200
I want you to go around Beijing and take pictures.
我想让你在北京四处走走，拍下照片。

77
00:04:35,520 --> 00:04:36,980
Again, the idea is contrast.
再次，核心是对比。

78
00:04:37,660 --> 00:04:41,100
Remember that here he says, New York is a city of things unnoticed.
记住这里他说：纽约是一座不被注意到的事物之城。

79
00:04:41,600 --> 00:04:43,720
New York is a city of contrast.
纽约是一座对比之城。

80
00:04:44,280 --> 00:04:46,680
I want you to do the same thing for Beijing.
我想让你在北京也做同样的事。

81
00:04:46,840 --> 00:04:49,420
Take your camera and take pictures of contrast.
拿起相机，拍下对比的画面。

82
00:04:49,420 --> 00:04:51,360
Things that other people would not notice.
别人不注意到的事物。

83
00:04:51,580 --> 00:04:55,880
Okay? And take pictures of things that are contrast of each other.
好的？再拍下互相对比的事物。
